## Technical Documentation: TAC/COM Field Radio v12.3

This document outlines the architecture, interface logic, and hardware specifications for the **TAC/COM v12.3 Bi-Directional Tuning System**.

---

### 1. System Overview
The TAC/COM v12.3 is a high-fidelity, Peer-to-Peer (P2P) communication interface designed for tactical web environments. It utilizes **PeerJS** and **MQTT** for real-time audio and text relays, wrapped in a "Retro-Cyber" hardware chassis.

### 2. Physical Interface Layout
The device follows a specific ergonomic layout to mimic field-grade hardware:

| Component | Description |
| :--- | :--- |
| **External Antenna** | Top-left stub for visual signal integrity. |
| **Signal RSSI Bars** | 5-stage intensity bars (Top-Left) indicating link quality. |
| **Rotary Nozzle** | Multi-function frequency dial (Top-Right) beside the Network LED. |
| **Speaker Grille** | Centrally located acoustic mesh to bridge structural gaps. |
| **Visual Scope** | Real-time waveform visualizer (Oscilloscope). |
| **PTT Lever** | Large tactical Push-To-Talk bar with mechanical depress logic. |

---

### 3. Core Functionality & Logic

#### A. Bi-Directional Rotary Tuning
The nozzle implements a coordinate-aware interaction model:
* **Clockwise ($\Delta \theta > 0$):** Triggered by clicking the **Right** hemisphere of the dial. Increments frequency by **1 MHz**.
* **Anticlockwise ($\Delta \theta < 0$):** Triggered by clicking the **Left** hemisphere. Decrements frequency by **1 MHz**.
* **Animation:** Uses CSS `transition` with a `cubic-bezier` timing function to simulate mechanical weight and snap.

#### B. Signal & Telemetry Logic
The indicators use a **Normalized Pulse Protocol** (Standard blinking without high-bloom glow):
* **Red Pulse:** System Offline / Hardware Standby.
* **Orange Pulse:** Synchronizing / Establishing Handshake.
* **Green Pulse:** Secure Link Established / Active Transmission.

#### C. Active Noise Cancellation (ANC)
The DSP filter layer (v12.3) applies a gate to the incoming audio buffer:
* **Threshold:** $0.02$ amplitude.
* **Logic:** If sample value $< 0.02$, the sample is flattened to $0$, effectively eliminating low-level background hiss and environmental "static."

---

### 4. Technical Specifications

* **Audio Sampling Rate ($SR$):** $12,000$ Hz (Optimized for low-bandwidth tactical clarity).
* **Encryption:** **AES-GCM (256-bit)** using PBKDF2 key derivation from the user-provided TAC-KEY.
* **Backend Protocol:** WSS (Secure WebSockets) via EMQX MQTT Broker.
* **Visual Framework:** HTML5 Canvas (Scanner Background & Scope Overlay).

---

### 5. Deployment Instructions
To deploy this system:
1.  Save the provided **Master HTML** code as a single `.html` file.
2.  Host on any static file server (e.g., **GitHub Pages**).
3.  Ensure the browser has granted **Microphone Access** permissions for the P2P relay to function.

> **Note:** For optimal performance across NAT firewalls, ensure the PeerJS configuration points to a valid STUN/TURN server if the default broker is congested.
